RAM KARAN & ORS V. STATE OF UTTAR PRADESH [1982] INSC 30; AIR 1982 SC 1185; 1982 (3) SCR 395; 1982 (2) SCC 184; 1982 (1) SCALE 288 (4 March 1982)

 FAZALALI, SYED MURTAZA FAZALALI, SYED MURTAZA DESAI, D.A.
 VARADARAJAN, A. (J) 
CITATION: 1982 AIR 1185 1982 SCR (3) 395 1982 SCC (2) 184 1982 SCALE (1)288 
ACT:
 Sentencing-Imposition of appropriate sentence, under section 302 or 304 depends on the nature of offence of culpable homicide-Evidence showing homicide by both parties in a Civil Suit in a sudden fight in the heat of passion upon a quarrel-Appropriate sentence would be one under sections 304(1)/34 Indian Penal Code and not under sections 302/34 Indian Penal Code-Probability of culpability not proved by legal evidence-Benefit of doubt must ensue in such cases.
 
